  ____________________________:________________________________
  [] The Accretia has strong solid mechanical body where stren-
     gth can be easily felt.  Although  they  cannot use force,
     their strong defense and supporting will lead them to bec-
     ome the supreme leaders of Novus.

  [] WHY DO THEY FIGHT?
  _____________________________________________________________
     >> The  Accretia Empire's  mechanically  engineered policy
        began with the goal of extending life, but slowly chan-
        ged into early dawn of  building a strong empire.  With
        one objective,  unified awareness  was the motive  that
        made the empire stronger. The empire  gave the citizens
        a way of thinking towards totalitarianism based on mate
        rialism,  and by doing so,  they dreamed of  building a
        stronger empire.
        The foundation of machine civilization was to constant-
        ly replicate production and consumption.Their route for
        expansion was obligatory for their existence.
        In the  long run,  their  choice  brought  chaos to the
        Novus Solar System.

  [] WHY DO THEY FIGHT?
  _____________________________________________________________
     >> The power of strong gravity made the Bellato's body sm-
        all, nevertheless, they were presented with exceptional
        physical strength.  With the  association of  dangerous
        natural environments that surrounds them, the civiliza-
        tion established rational and various mental abilities.
        Such abilities  were enhanced through the trade between
        the Accretia Empire's machine civilization and the Cora
        holy alliance's spiritual civilization, making the Bel-
        latons  rule  over unique grounds full of  machines and
        spirituality combined.  And now,  all they have left to
        do is destroy both  Corans  and  Accretians in order to
        hold the supreme power of Novus solar system.
        In the end,  Bellatons'  endless  thirst for  expansion
        changed.

  [] WHY DO THEY FIGHT?
  _____________________________________________________________
     >> The Corans who worship Decem,  the god of numbers,  has
        undergone contradictions due to religious proclamation.
        It was called the 'war of color', which lead victory to
        dark classes. After the war, a single pope took the ce-
        nter of this strong religion and established a holy al-
        ly named 'Cora'.  The most importantvalue for Corans is
        practicing the will  throughout the universe,  which is
        from the godlike perfect ones who are called Decem.  To
        conquer the Solar System and earning supreme power, pr-
        opagating  by the  military  force was merely a part of
        Decem's will. However, the propagation of religion whi-
        ch started the waris now an inevitable conflict in ord-
        er to survive.

  | ** Cora HQ/Outpost map Quick Reference Guide              |
  :===========================================================:
  |                                                           |
  | <> - Passage to Neutral settlement area                   |
  |      ** going to Haram Sector direction                   |
  |                                                           |
  | C1 - Trust a.k.a. CLIENT in Hunter Cave                   |
  |                                                           |
  | C2 - Ordinary a.k.a. CLIENT in Dark Plain                 |
  |                                                           |
  | ET - PAYBOX NPC                                           |
  |      ** buy ticket here to go to Ether in the Sky         |
  |                                                           |
  | N] - North Cave Entrance                                  |
  |      ** going inside Hunter Cave                          |
  |                                                           |
  | PA - Alliance HQ Portal                                   |
  |      ** going to Alliance OutpostPortal, CragMine Alliance|
  |         Portal, Haram Citadel, Numerous Citadel, and Sette|
  |         Desert                                            |
  |                                                           |
  | PH - Alliance Outpost Portal                              |
  |      ** going to Cora HQ                                  |
  |                                                           |
  | SW - SouthWest Cave Entrance                              |
  |      ** going inside Hunter Cave                          |
  |                                                           |
  | T1 - TOOL NPC in Spire Plain                              |
  |                                                           |
  | T2 - TOOL NPC in Spire Forest                             |
  |                                                           |
  | T3 - TOOL NPC in Spire Forest                             |
  |                                                           |
  | WD - Wave of Dimension                                    |

  |                                                           |

  :===========================================================:
//| ** Jewelry and Lucky Cubes                                |
v :===========================================================:
|
| [] Upon reaching level 50, your character is obliged to acco-
|    mplish what everyone calls "the Unseal Quest". A series of
|    mobs to eradicate like Calianas, Red Haired Splinter,  and
|    so on and so forth. The last part of this infamous "Unseal
|    Quest" obliges you secure these seals [Seal of Blood, Seal
|    of Destruction, and Seal of Soul].
|    The easiest way to get these seals is to destroy  at least
|    1 piece Jewelry Cube since these seals are this cube's dr-
|    op items.  These cubes can be found in Beast's Mountain.
|
|    Most gamers believe that these Jewelry Cubes & Lucky Cubes
|    respawn at total random or no specific spot(s).  Truth  is
|    these hard to find cubes has it's own specific respawn sp-
|    ots. While we're still trying to get most, if not all, re-
|    spawn spots for these cubes -> you may want to try some of
|    spots we got.
|
|    >> Jewelry Cube [Normal/Mutant/Fire] locations:
|
|       - Ancient's Road: 40 53
|       - Ancient's Road: 67 52 [near Dragon's Grave part]
|       - Ancient's Road: 70 53

|         31 31

  | ** INTRODUCTION TO RF ONLINE SPECIAL QUESTS **            |
  :===========================================================:

  [] As you level your character, you are introduced to in-game
     quests which automatically show on your quests window. Ac-
     complishing these quests provide your character rewards in
     form of character experience, armors, weird items, or even
     in-game race currencies. If you are quite lazy - don't bo-
     ther taking these quests.

     On the other hand  RF Online  offers another type of quest
     your character might want to take advantage of; gamers us-
     ually call this as "NPC quests" ----- simply because these
     quests are given by  different NPCs  at certain  character
     levels.  These quests  will not  show on your quest window
     since your character will need to get  them from  specific 
     NPC(s) as you level up.
     The in-game quests window calls these as "Special Orders".
     Accomplishing these Special Orders should give your chara-
     better rewards [as compared to the normal quests mentioned
     above] most of the time, like: Jade of Vitality, 5% EXP p-
     otions, etc... Although some rewards are not worth it, li-
     ke killing a pitboss  in exchange of  1pc Keen, Favor,  or
     whatever talic. Nevertheless, the main reason why you mig-
     ht want to take advantage of Special Orders is - these qu-
     ests contain half of each race's story in RF Online world.
     Thus,  if you want to know why there are "Deserted"-"other
     race's" mob roaming around near your race's HQ; you'll ne-
     ed to play these Special Orders.

  [] NOTE for special Quests:
     Let's say your special quest  tells you to  collect 20 pcs
     of Unstable Ruy Mica. You then collected 20 pcs of it.  If
     you sell these 20 pcs Unstable Ruy Mica to an NPC --- your
     quest window will still say you've already got 20 pcs; but
     the NPC where you need to bring these  loots won't respond
     if you click the CONVERSATION button. You will need to re-
     collect another 20pcs  to complete  the quest. Thus, never
     sell your Special Quest loots right away until you've che-
     cked with the requesting NPC.

|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | White Excelsior:                                   |
|        | Holy Force Reavers                                 |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Yellow Excelsior:                                  |
|        | Launcher Type Weapons                              |
|        |                                                    |
:=============================================================:
| What excelsior to use on specific weapon levels             |
:=============================================================:
| Level 30 and 35 Weapons need 1 Type A Excelsior             |
| Level 40 Weapons need 1 Type B Excelsior                    |
| Level 45 WEapons need 1 Type C Excelsior                    |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:



:=============================================================:
| TYPE A WEAPONS + TYPE B WEAPONS = TYPE C WEAPONS            |
:=============================================================:
|Requirements:                                                |
|   Type A Weapon (Purple)                                    |
| + Type B weapon of the same kind (Intense)                  |
| + Corresponding Complete Excelsior depending on weapon      |
| + 100,000 combining fee for Hero NPC                        |
| ------------------------------------------                  |
| = Type C weapon (Orange)                                    |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|Example:                                                     |
|   Sharp Gatling Gun (LV35)                                  |
| + Intense Gatling Gun (LV35)                                |
| + Type B Red Excelsior (Check next chart below why Type B)  |
| + 100,000 combining fee for Hero NPC                        |
| ------------------------------------------                  |
| = Sharp Intense Gatling Gun (LV requirement varies)         |
|                                                             |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                                             |
| ** All requirements above (x1) each...                      |
| ** Type A Weapons can be purchased from Type A Weapon Vendor|
|    NPC in HQ; or may be in a form of drop items from mobs...|
| ** Type B Weapons can be purchased from Type B Weapon Vendor|
|    NPC in HQ; or may be in a form of drop items from mobs...|
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:





:=============================================================:
| EXTRACT ABILITIES FROM TYPE A (PURPLE) WEAPONS:             |
:=============================================================:
|   Type A Weapon (x1)                                        |
| + Ability Extractor (x1)                                    |
| + Restoration Talic (x1)                                    |
| -------------------                                         |
| = Ability Reaver (x1)                                       |
|                                                             |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                                             |
| ** Type A Weapons can be purchased from Type A Weapon Vendor|
|    NPC in HQ...                                             |
| ** Ability Extractor can be purchased from TOOL NPC in HQ...|
| ** Restoration Talics can be acquired through mining; or by |
|    purchasing them from other players who may have it...    |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:





:=============================================================:
| MAKE TYPE A (PURPLE) WEAPONS OUT OF NORMAL WEAPONS:         |
:=============================================================:
|   Normal Weapon (x1)                                        |
| + Ability Combiner (x1)                                     |
| + Talic (x1)                                                |
| + Ability (x1)                                              |
| + Purple Complete Excelsior A (x1)                          |
| -----------------------------                               |
| = Type A Weapon (x1)                                        |
|                                                             |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                                             |
| ** Normal Weapons can be purchased from NPC in HQ; or may be|
|    in a form of loots from your typical ingame mob...       |
| ** Ability Combiner can be purchased from TOOL NPC in HQ... |
| ** Talics can be acquired through mining; or by purchasing  |
|    them from other players who may have it...               |
| ** Ability can be acquired from Inventor's Accessory Box... |
|                                                             |
| ** [Ability and Talic Combination]                          |
|    ++ For ability combining Type A Purple Excelsior is al-  |
|       ways used:                                            |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||   ABILITY                    TALIC                        ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
|    Wind/Protection            Belief                        |
|    Endurance                  SacredFire                    |
|    Fine                       Grace                         |
|    Smart                      Mercy                         |
|    Strong                     Ignorant                      |
|    Solid                      Favor                         |
|    Saving                     Darkness                      |
|    Strength                   Glory                         |
|    Advanced Strength          Guard                         |
|    Vampire                    Destruction                   |
|    Guardran                   Wisdom                        |
|    Sharp/Anti-sharp           Chaos                         |
|    Grand                      Hatred                        |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:

:=============================================================:

| + 99 Purple Excelsiar Pieces                                |
| + 01 Type C Purple                                          |
| + 10 Armor Ability items                                    |
| + 01 Intense Armor with +1 to +5 favor upgrades...          |
| + Combining fee for Hero NPC                                |

:=============================================================:
| Talic List                                                  |
:=============================================================:
| Talics have various uses, they are commonly used in the     |
| upgrading of items. However they are also needed for creat- |
| ing certain items, for example, force reavers.              |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Restoration Talic:                                 |
|        | Removes Last Talic from Armour/Weapon              |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Force Reavers: Holy Force Reavers (Bell Only)      |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Keen Talic:                                        |
|        | Upgrading: All Weapons Increases Attack by         |
|        | 5%, 13%, 25%, 50%, 80%, 135%, 200% per talic       |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Strong                          |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Favor Talic:                                       |
|        | Upgrading: Armour - Increases Defence by           |
|        | 5%, 13%, 25%, 50%, 80%, 135%, 200% per talic       |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Solid                           |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Chaos Talic:                                       |
|        | Upgrading: Weapons Increases Stun Chance           |
|        | 10%, 15%, 20%, 25%, 30%, 35%, 50% per talic        |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Strong                          |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Jetpack Crafting: Anti Crit                        |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Mercy Talic:                                       |
|        | Upgrading: Boots, Increases Dodge                  |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Smart                           |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Darkness Talic:                                    |
|        | Upgrading: Gloves Decreases Block Rate             |
|        | 2%, 5%, 10%, 12%, 15%, 20%, 25% per talic          |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Saving                          |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Force Reavers: Dark Force Reavers (Cora Only)      |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Grace Talic:                                       |
|        | Upgrading: Gloves, Increases Accuracy              |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Fine                            |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Destruction Talic:                                 |
|        | Upgrading: Weapons Converts % of Damage to HP      |
|        | 10%, 20%, 30%, 45%, 60%, 75%, 100% per talic       |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Vampire                         |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Hatred Talic:                                      |
|        | Upgrading: Ranged Weapon, Increases Range          |
|        | 10, 20, 30, 45, 60, 75, 100 per talic              |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Grand                           |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Wisdom Talic:                                      |
|        | Upgrading: Helment, Decreases duration of debuffs  |
|        | 10, 20, 30, 45, 60, 75, 100 per talic              |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Guardian                        |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Glory Talic:                                       |
|        | Upgrading: All Weapons Change to Wind Element      |
|        | Upgrading: Armour - Increase Wind Resistace        |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Strength                        |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Force Reavers: Wind Force Reavers (Bell/Cora)      |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Jetpack Crafting: Wind Resistace                   |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Guard Talic:                                       |
|        | Upgrading: All Weapons Change to Terra Element     |
|        | Upgrading: Armour - Increase Terra Resistace       |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Adv Strength                    |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Force Reavers: Terra Force Reavers (Bell/Cora)     |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Jetpack Crafting: Terra Resistace                  |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Sacredfire Talic:                                  |
|        | Upgrading: All Weapons Change to Fire Element      |
|        | Upgrading: Armour - Increase Fire Resistace        |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Endurance                       |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Force Reavers: Fire Force Reavers (Bell/Cora)      |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Jetpack Crafting: Fire Resistace                   |
|        |                                                    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|        | Belief Talic:                                      |
|        | Upgrading: All Weapons Change to Water Element     |
|        | Upgrading: Armour - Increase Aqua Resistace        |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Ability Combining: Protection, Wind                |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Force Reavers: Water Force Reavers (Bell/Cora)     |
|        |                                                    |
|        | Jetpack Crafting: Aqua Resistace                   |
|        |                                                    |

|------------------|                     |--------------------|

| Hatred           |                     | Yellow Chip        |
|------------------|                     |--------------------|
| Wisdom           |                     | Yellow Chip        |

|    amount of racial current...                              |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||   CHIP                    WHEN SOLD TO NPC                ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
| >> Red Chip        =       approx: 4,285,500                |
| >> Blue Chip       =       approx: 2,571,300                |
| >> Orange Chip     =       approx: 1,714,200                |
| >> Yellow Chip     =       approx:   857,100                |
|                                                             |
| ** Figures above may depend on ingame racial currency Econo-|
|    mic fluctuations...                                      |

:=============================================================:
| Mysterious Boxes from Keen and Favor Talics                 |
:=============================================================:
| ** There is an option in TALIC COLLECTOR NPC to  swap Favor |
|    or Keen Talics with Mysterious Boxes.                    |
|                                                             |
| ** At time of writing there are two kind of Mysterious box: |
|    ++ [Mysterious TreasureBox[Defense]]                     |
|       >> from swapping Favor Talics:                        |
|          ** may give out: Favor Talics,  Leon's Boxes,  EXP |
|             recovery pills, superior and intense armors.    |
|                                                             |
|    ++ [Mysterious TreasureBox[Offense]]                     |
|       >> from swapping Keen Talics:                         |
|          ** may give out: Keen Talics,   Leon's Boxes,  EXP |
|             recovery pills, superior and intense armors.    |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:




:=============================================================:
|   Favor Talic (x1)                                          |
| + Processing Fee for Hero NPC                               |
| --------------------------------------                      |
| = 1 ea. of Mercy, Grace, Wisdom, Darkness, and Chaos Talics |
:=============================================================:




:=============================================================:
|   Talics of any kind (x20)                                  |
| + TALIC COLLECTOR NPC's intervention                        |
| --------------------------------------                      |
| = Talic Crystal (x1)                                        |
|   ** along with racial currency; can be exchanged for supe- |
|      rior armors  (at time of writing)  through AMBASSADORS |
|      NPC in HQ.                                             |
|   ** may also be exchanged for Novajan's Ancient Remain bo- |
|      xes that may give out  different  runes,  relic items, |
|      EXP recovery pills,  intense and superior  weapons and |
|      armors.                                                |
:=============================================================:




:=============================================================:
|   Talic Crystal (x2)                                        |
| + Processing Fee for Hero NPC                               |
| --------------------------------------                      |
| = Compressed Talic Crystal (x1)                             |
|   ** along with racial currency; can be exchanged for high- |
|      level armors (at time of writing) through DRAGONKNIGHT |
|      NPC in HQ.                                             |
:=============================================================:





:=============================================================:
| LEVELS 40, 50, 55, AND 60 JETPACKS                          |
:=============================================================:
| ** As your character reach level 40 - you may now wear what |
|    they call "jetpack". These speed booster can be acquired |
|    through crafting or simply purchasing it from other pla- |
|    yers who sells it.                                       |
| ** Jetpacks provide more elemental resistance for you char- |
|    acter.                                                   |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||Crafting the LV40 Jetpack:                                 ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
|   Type A, B, or C Olive Excelsior (x1)                      |
| + Bag (x1)                                                  |
| + Beam (x99)                                                |
| + Gli (x99)                                                 |
| + Talic (x1)                                                |
| + Combining fee for Hero NPC                                |
| ------------------------------                              |
| = Jetpack (x1)                                              |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||Crafting the LV50 Jetpack:                                 ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
|   Type A, B, or C Olive Excelsior (x5)                      |
| + Bag (x1)                                                  |
| + Beam (x99)                                                |
| + Gli (x99)                                                 |
| + Talic (x1)                                                |
| + Combining fee for Hero NPC                                |
| ------------------------------                              |
| = Jetpack (x1)                                              |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||Crafting the LV55 Jetpack:                                 ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
| ** No info known yet...                                     |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||Crafting the LV60 Jetpack:                                 ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
| ** No info known yet...                                     |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
||CRAFTING JETPACK NOTES:                                    ||
||                                                           ||
||** As mentioned above;  Types A, B, or C  Olive Excelsiors ||
||   are used for crafting these jetpacks. Type C Olive Exc- ||
||   elsiors will give you the higher chance of crafting one ||
||   but take note "higher chance" don't mean "100% chance". ||
||   Also, the Hero NPC fee for combining the above-mention- ||
||   ed components  vary with each Type of  Olive Excelsiors ||
||   used.                                                   ||
||                                                           ||
||** LV40 jetpack combining fee goes as follows:             ||
||   ++ Unconfirmed yet if this changes as ingame Economy fl-||
||      uctuates...                                          ||
||   >> Type A: approx. 09 million racial currency           ||
||   >> Type B: approx. 15 million racial currency           ||
||   >> Type C: approx. 22 million racial currency           ||
||                                                           ||
||** LV50 jetpack combining fee goes as follows:             ||
||   ++ Unconfirmed yet if this changes as ingame Economy fl-||
||      uctuates...                                          ||
||   >> Type A: approx. 12 million racial currency           ||
||   >> Type B: approx. 20 million racial currency           ||
||   >> Type C: approx. 30 million racial currency           ||
||                                                           ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
:=============================================================:




:=============================================================:
|   Halostone Pieces (x99)                                    |
| + 1,000,000 Combining Fee for Hero NPC                      |
| --------------------------------------                      |
| = Complete Halostone (x1)                                   |
:=============================================================:

| = Riar  (x random)                                          |

  [X] Crafting and other stuff

  [X] Repeatable Quests with/without cooldown and Bugged Quests

:=============================================================:
| Overview :: Repeatable Quests without cooldown              |
:=============================================================:
| ** These are the quests you can take advantage of from time |
|    to time.                                                 |
|    The most "controversial" Quest NPC found near Novas Tree |
|    may provide you these quests so long  as  your character |
|    matches these levels: 49 - 55.                           |
|    Since you can cancel these quests anytime, and you still |
|    can get it in the future with no cooldown time; thus du- |
|    bbed it "Repeatable Quests".                             |
|                                                             |
| ++ HOW TO GET THESE REPEATABLE QUESTS WITHOUT COOLDOWN:     |
|    (1) Proceed to 64 28 Novas Tree in Elan;  click on TRADE |
|        so you can see the  DNA Sampling booties this NPC is |
|        vending.                                             |
|    (2) After acquiring the DNA Sampling booty/ies which has |
|        your preferred quest. Click the QUEST option of this |
|        same NPC (Quest NPC).                                |
|        Your SPECIAL ORDERS portion on your character's jou- |
|        rnal will then be updated by quests you've chosen/p- |
|        urchased.                                            |
|    (3) Take the quest by accomplishing what needs accompli- |
|        shment, then "craft" the requested quest item before |
|        going back to the same NPC (Quest NPC) for CONVERSA- |
|        TION to get your rewards.                            |
|                                                             |
| ++ REWARDS FROM THESE REPEATABLE QUESTS WITHOUT COOLDOWN:   |
|    (1) 300 PvP points                                       |
|        >> Self-explanatory.                                 |
|    (2) Small EXP Gain Potion                                |
|        >> Provides .1000 experience points for your charac- |
|           ter.                                              |
|    (3) DNA Capsule corresponding the quest                  |
|        >> Potion with different effects. Pleease check bel- |
|           ow for specific details.                          |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:
|    You may choose from these 10 "DNA Sampling" booties:     |
:=============================================================:
\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/

:=============================================================:
| Overview :: Repeatable Quests with 24-hour cooldown         |
:=============================================================:
| ** Upon reaching LV 51,  there will be two quests available |
|    at your disposal. Each quest will provide you 1.5 exper- |
|    ience potion per completion.                             |
|    These quests can only be  taken once every after 24-hour |
|    time frame.                                              |
|                                                             |
| ** Each race has 2 of these repeatable quests. Thus, you'll |
|    get 2 pcs. 1.5 experiece potion when these two are acco- |
|    mplished. Think of it as 3 experience points per day on- |
|    ce your character drank these two experience potions.    |
|    Not bad since it is quite  difficult to gain  experience |
|    oints when your character reaches  level 51 -(at time of |
|    this writing)-  unless you have stunner weapons that al- |
|    lows you to do solo battle dungeon.                      |
|                                                             |
| ++ HOW TO!?:                                                |
|    >> Nothing fancy; just accomplish these quests, grab the |
|       rewards. Then wait for 24 hours, and redo same quests |
|       after 24 hours; and so on and so forth.... until your |
|       character reaches LV56.                               |
|                                                             |
|       [For Accretia]                                        |
|       (1) Operation N (Person of Merit NPC)                 |
|       (2) Deposit Information (WEAPON TYPE B NPC)           |
|                                                             |
|       [For Bellato]                                         |
|       (1) |
|       (2) |
|                                                             |
|       [For Cora]                                            |
|       (1) |
|       (2) |
:=============================================================:




:=============================================================:
| Overview :: Repeatable Quests without 24-hour cooldown      |
:=============================================================:
| ** If you've been doing these repeatable quests for  3 or 4 |
|    days, the 24-hour cooldown period will disappear.  Thus, |
|    you will have unlimited repeatable quests.               |
|                                                             |
| ** Think of it as repeatedly  accomplishing two quests that |
|    gives your character 2 pcs. 1.5 experience potions after |
|    completion (of these two quests); which means - experie- |
|    nce potions anytime you like.                            |
|                                                             |
| ++ HOW TO!?:                                                |
|    >> Nothing fancy; just keep doing the "Repeatable Quests |
|       with 24-hour cooldown" for 3 or 4 days;  and cooldown |
|       period should disappear thereby allowing your charac- |
|       ter to take unlimited quests everyday.                |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:




:=============================================================:
| Overview ::                                                 |
| Bugged Repeatable Quests with and without 24-hour cooldown  |
:=============================================================:
| ** These are  technically the same  "Repeatable Quests with |
|    or without 24-hour cooldown"  mentioned above -  but the |
|    main reason it was dubbed as "Bugged Quests"  or "BQ" is |
|    that:                                                    |
|    because of a certain in-game process; you're able to ac- |
|    complish two same quests per quest run. Unclear!? Let me |
|    explain more:                                            |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (1)Try to imagine the Quests window -  this is the one that |
|    appears whenever "J" is pressed while on "Keyboard Mode" |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (2)Say you'd like the  "Deposit Information"  quest bugged. |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (3)Normally, the order of this quest would be like this:    |
|    *====================================================*   |
|       -- after getting the quest from NPC your special --   |
|       -- quest window will show quests in these order. --   |
|                                                             |
|    1st: Deposit Information                                 |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|    2nd: Finding Deposit                                     |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|    3rd: Finding Deposit(2)                                  |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|    4th: Searching Ether Deposit                             |
|                                                             |
|       -- you will get  1 piece 1.5 experience potion  --    |
|       -- after accomplishing Searching Ether Deposit. --    |
|    *====================================================*   |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (4)If bugged, the order of the quests should look like:     |
|    *====================================================*   |
|       -- after getting the quest from NPC your special --   |
|       -- quest window will show quests in these order. --   |
|                                                             |
|    1st: Deposit Information                                 |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|    2nd: Finding Deposit                                     |
|             -and-                                           |
|         Deposit Information                                 |
|       **============================================**      |
|       || Technically, you will still be in the same ||      |
|       || place where the mobs for Deposit Informat- ||      |
|       || ion will be.                               ||      |
|       || Think of this as accomplishing Deposit In- ||      |
|       || formation quest twice.                     ||      |
|       || Do the Deposit Information Quest again.    ||      |
|       **============================================**      |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|    3rd: Finding Deposit                                     |
|             -and-                                           |
|         Finding Deposit                                     |
|       **============================================**      |
|       || You'll notice the same quest will be doub- ||      |
|       || led. Killing 1 Hidden Soldier will  give 1 ||      |
|       || kill count on these 2 same quests.         ||      |
|       **============================================**      |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|    4th: Finding Deposit(2)                                  |
|             -and-                                           |
|         Finding Deposit(2)                                  |
|                                                             |
|       -- once done; special quests window will show --      |
|                                                             |
|    5th: Searching Ether Deposit                             |
|             -and-                                           |
|         Searching Ether Deposit                             |
|                                                             |
|       -- you will get 2 pieces 1.5 experience potions  --   |
|       -- after accomplishing Searching Ether Deposit. --    |
|    *====================================================*   |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| TAKE NOTE!!!                                                |
|    ** Once you're done with all the quests - you'll be rew- |
|       awarded with 2 EXP Potions worth 1.5 EXP points each. |
|       Notifications should appear on the lower right corner |
|       of your screen.                                       |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|    ** Don't get all the EXP Potions right away. Why!? Beca- |
|       use if you accept all right away what will happen is: |
|       These EXP potions will disappear  from your inventory |
|       after 7 minutes. 1 EXP potion will also have a 7 min- |
|       ute cooldown period  before you  can  use another EXP |
|       potion. Thus, if you have 2 EXP Potions in your inve- |
|       ntory and you used 1 you won't be able to use another |
|       EXP Potion within the next 7 minutes.                 |
|       Then after 7 minutes, and the second potion  is still |
|       present in your inventory - it will disappear.        |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
|    ** Thus, correct way is to accept 1 EXP Potion first fr- |
|       the quest notification  -(on the lower right corner)- |
|       and wait for 7 minutes; then that's the right time to |
|       accept the second EXP Potion from the quest notifica- |
|       tion.                                                 |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:
| How to bug these repeatable quests:                         |
:=============================================================:
| (1)Go to Quest NPC located in Novas Tree -- this is the NPC |
|    that sells the repeatable DNA Quests.                    |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (2)Purchase  5  of  any of these DNA Quests, and then click |
|    Quest NPC's Quest menu to take the 5 DNA quests you pur- |
|    chased. 5 DNA Quests should appear on your "Special Ord- |
|    er's" window. Press "J" while on  keyboard mode to go to |
|    display your Special Quests window.                      |
|    ** Approx: pricing will depend on ecomnomy of your char- |
|       acter's race.                                         |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (3)Now that your Special Order's window is filled  with DNA |
|    Quests. You may now go to the NPC that offers the respe- |
|    ctive quests that can be bugged.                         |
|                                                             |
|    For Accretia as an example:                              |
|    ** You can go to Person of Merit  if you want to bug the |
|       Operation-N Quest.                                    |
|                                                             |
|    ** You can go to Weapon Type B if you want to bug the    |
|       Finding Deposit Quest.                                |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (4)Once you're with either Person of Merit or Weapon Type B |
|    you must pick the quest (Operation-N or Finding Deposit) |
|    7 times.  Of course you won't be able to since your Spe- |
|    cial Orders window is filled with unfinished DNA QUests. |
|    But just pick it 7 times even if it is not allowing you. |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (5)Then after the 7 times thing - cancel all the unfinished |
|    DNA Quests  in your Special Order's window.  And, again, |
|    pick  the  repeatable quest  (Operation-N if you're with |
|    Person of Merit or Finding Deposit if you're with Weapon |
|    Type B).                                                 |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
| (6)Finish the quests and enjoy the  EXP Potions.  Take note |
|    that  these  EXP Potions  will have a 7 minute timeframe |
|    before it disappears from your inventory --- so use them |
|    right away.                                              |
|                                                             |
|                                                             |
:=============================================================:

| GM Commands                                                 |
:=============================================================:
| ** Commands for use on Private Servers                      |
|                                                             |
|.-----------------------------------------------------------.|
|| Basic Commands                                            ||
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
|                                                             |
|  !chathere	Notice Chat(GM Character Only)                |
|  #chathere	GM Only Chat                                  |
|                                                             |
|  %move XXXX               Teleport to XXXX Character        |
|  %jump MapName X Y Z      Teleport to Specific XYZ          |
|                                                             |
|  %port 00-03              Teleport to HQ Port               |
|                           + Bellato  = 00                   |
|                           + Accretia = 01                   |
|                           + Cora     = 02                   |
|                                                             |
|  %moncall 00000 XX        Spawns monster XX = Amount        |
|  %neverdie                HP Auto Regen and Fixed SP,FP     |
|                                                             |
|  %beggar                  Monster Drops Everything          |
|  %no beggar               Turns off Beggar                  |
|                                                             |
|  %matchless               Hit target for total HP           |
|  %no matchless            Turns off Matchless               |
|                                                             |
|  %transparent             Invisible to Normal Players       |
|  %no transparent          Turns off Invisibility            |
|                                                             |
|  %god hand                100% Upgrading                    |
|  %chicken hand            Regular Upgrading                 |
|                                                             |
|'-----------------------------------------------------------'|
